SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 58
BY SENATORS JACKSON-ANDREWS, CATHEY AND MORRIS
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Recognizes Tuesday, April 7, 2026, as Coca-Cola Day
at the Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To recognize Tuesday, April 7, 2026, as Coca-Cola Day at the Louisiana State Capitol and
3 to commend Coca-Cola UNITED for its outstanding legacy, economic impact, and
4 enduring commitment to the residents and communities of Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, Coca-Cola UNITED's story in Louisiana began in 1902, in the city of
6 New Orleans as Crescent City Coca-Cola, soon followed by the Baton Rouge Coca-Cola
7 Bottling Company in 1906, with both locations establishing a cornerstone for a company that
8 would grow to become an integral part of Louisiana's economic and cultural fabric; and
9 WHEREAS, for more than one hundred twenty-four years, Coca-Cola UNITED, now
10 a vital, privately owned Coca-Cola bottler, has proudly operated in Louisiana, continuously
11 expanding its offerings to a diverse portfolio of more than seven hundred fifty beverage
12 options along with a growing emphasis on low-calorie and sugar-free choices, reflecting its
13 commitment to evolving consumer needs and health-conscious lifestyles; and
14 WHEREAS, Coca-Cola UNITED currently operates seven facilities throughout
15 Louisiana, including five sales and distribution centers and two production plants, providing
16 meaningful employment to over two thousand three hundred dedicated Louisianians and
17 contributing significantly to the state's economy; and
18 WHEREAS, as a locally owned and operated employer, Coca-Cola UNITED sustains
